# Material semantics — adoption contract

**Canonical sources of truth (in order):**

1. **`app/globals.css`** — material tokens, phase classes, Lynx state classes (the engineering implementation)
2. **`docs/decisions/0001-afenda-spatial-os-shell.md`** §12 (spatial conformance) + §13 (material semantics adoption)
3. **`AGENTS.md` §7** — design system row

This rule mirrors those sources. If they diverge, **`globals.css`** + **ADR-0001** win and this rule must be repaired in the same change.

> Material semantics is **shell infrastructure**, not generic UI styling. Buttons, forms, tables, lists, and dense ERP content remain stable and readable. Cognition (water) is **not** a reading layer.

---

## 1. Material phase model (4 phases — the only ones that exist)

| Phase | Class | When it applies |
| ---- | ---- | ---- |
| `shell` | `.af-material-shell` | idle, settled (default for chrome) |
| `transition` | `.af-material-transition` *(or shell + `data-phase="hover|focus|typing"`)* | activation threshold |
| `cognition` | `.af-material-cognition` *(or shell + `data-phase="resolving|execution"`)* | truth resolution surface |
| `cognition+` | shell + `data-lynx="high-confidence"` | confidence-deepened cognition |

Plus one read-only variant:

- `.af-material-opaque` — **REQUIRED** for dense reading surfaces (tables, ledgers, audit logs, evidence timelines, ERP forms)

Do not invent additional phase classes or data attribute values. Phase mutation happens via attributes; classes are stable.

---

## 2. Runtime state machine (the only allowed `data-phase` values)

```txt
idle -> hover -> focus -> typing -> resolving -> execution -> settled
```

`data-phase` mapping is enforced in `app/globals.css`:

```tsx
<div
  className="af-material af-material-shell"
  data-phase={phase}                     // idle | hover | focus | typing | resolving | execution | settled
  data-current={isCurrent ? "on" : undefined}
  data-lynx={lynxState}                  // idle | listening | resolving | high-confidence | warning | mismatch
/>
```

Forbidden: ad-hoc state names (`active`, `selected`, `open`, `loading`, `processing`, `ai`, `aiActive`). Map runtime state to one of the canonical phase values; do not add more selectors.

---

## 3. Lynx material-aware vocabulary

| `data-lynx` | Meaning |
| ---- | ---- |
| `idle` | shell |
| `listening` | transition (refraction) |
| `resolving` | cognition |
| `high-confidence` | deeper saturation |
| `warning` | brief pressure pulse + persistent warning outline |
| `mismatch` | brief unstable refraction + persistent skewed flow angle |

Banned user-facing labels: **AI mode**, **AI active**, **Thinking**, **Processing**, **Generating**. Use **resolving**, **listening**, **high confidence**, **warning**, **mismatch** (operational vocabulary). Mirrors `.cursor/rules/lynx-directory.mdc`.

---

## 4. Surface adoption table (which surface gets which material)

| Surface | Allowed material |
| ---- | ---- |
| Utility bar (L1) | `shell` only |
| Dock (L4) | `shell` + `current` |
| Command palette (L3) | `shell` -> `transition` -> `cognition` |
| Lynx resolution surfaces | `cognition` (via `data-lynx`) |
| Modals | `shell` or `transition` |
| Toasts | `shell` only |
| Evidence cards | restrained `cognition` (do **not** escalate to high-confidence by default) |
| Workspace container | `shell` only |
| Dense tables / ledgers / inventory grids | `opaque` only |
| ERP forms | `opaque` or light `shell` |
| Audit logs / evidence timelines | `opaque` only |

Violations require an ADR-0001 amendment in the same change.

---

## 5. Token vocabulary (engineering)

Public philosophy still says "glass / water" in docs and ADRs. **Engineering tokens are operational:**

- `--af-glass-bg` (shell surface)
- `--af-cognition-1`, `--af-cognition-2` (chromatic anchors)
- `--af-resolution-surface` (cognition surface)
- `--af-blur-shell`, `--af-blur-command`, `--af-blur-resolution` (the three blur tiers)
- Nexus chrome utilities ( **`components/nexus/`** only — defined in `app/globals.css`): `.af-nexus-l1-chrome-backplate` (L1 shell-tier glass tint + blur; pair `.af-nexus-utility-bar-backdrop` on the bar for the bottom edge only), `.af-nexus-popover-panel` (floating panels → command tier), `.af-nexus-round-control-backdrop` (icon-only round controls → shell tier). Do **not** use Tailwind `backdrop-blur-*` there — CI enforces via `scripts/check-design-contract.mjs`.
- `--af-sat-shell`, `--af-sat-command`, `--af-sat-resolution`
- `--af-depth-shell`, `--af-depth-transition`, `--af-depth-resolution`
- `--af-flow-angle`, `--af-flow-velocity-*`
- `--motion-category-shell|command|resolution|pressure`
- `--af-ripple-strength`, `--af-current-strength`

Forbidden in TSX class strings, inline styles, and CSS modules: literal **`water`** in identifiers (`water-card`, `bg-water`, `water-mode`, etc.). Use the operational tokens above.

---

## 6. Forbidden patterns (enforced by `scripts/check-design-contract.mjs`)

Outside `app/globals.css`, do not introduce:

```ts
// JSX inline style — bypasses material governance
style={{ backdropFilter: "blur(20px)" }}
style={{ willChange: "backdrop-filter" }}
```

```html
<!-- Tailwind arbitrary blur — bypasses the 3-tier budget -->
<div className="backdrop-blur-[18px]" />
<div className="blur-[24px]" />
```

```html
<!-- Tailwind scaled backdrop-blur-* — forbidden under components/nexus/ -->
<div className="backdrop-blur-2xl" />
<!-- Use .af-nexus-l1-chrome-backplate (+ .af-nexus-utility-bar-backdrop on L1 bar) | .af-nexus-popover-panel | .af-nexus-round-control-backdrop -->
```

```css
/* Permanent motion is GPU + cognitive fatigue (HIG: continuous motion must be rare) */
animation: my-pulse 2s ease infinite;
```

Also forbidden: legacy renamed identifiers (drift detector):

- `--af-water-*` (renamed to `--af-cognition-*` / `--af-resolution-*` / `--af-blur-resolution` / `--af-sat-resolution` / `--af-depth-resolution`)
- `.af-material-water` (renamed to `.af-material-cognition`)
- `.af-material-transitioning` (renamed to `.af-material-transition`)

`will-change`, `backdrop-filter`, blur tier values, and infinite animations live **only** in `app/globals.css` and are scoped to active material phases there.

---

## 7. Animation discipline

- Continuous motion is rare (Apple HIG).
- State pulses (`af-pressure-pulse`, `af-unstable-refraction`) fire **3 iterations on entry, then settle**.
- Persistent state must be communicated by **static styling** (`outline`, `border-color`, skewed `--af-flow-angle`), not by an infinite animation.
- All animations respect `prefers-reduced-motion: reduce`.

---

## 8. Performance discipline

- `.af-material` uses `contain: paint`. Do not strip it.
- `.af-material-opaque` uses `contain: layout paint`.
- `will-change` is scoped via `:is()` to active phases only — never apply globally, never set via JSX style.
- Backdrop fallback under `@supports not (backdrop-filter)` is owned by `app/globals.css`.

---

## 9. CI gate

```bash
pnpm lint   # runs scripts/check-design-contract.mjs (material patterns + token parity)
```

The check fails on any banned pattern listed in §6 outside `app/globals.css`.
